<Author>SJW_1982
<Content>Hmm..... We expected a lower standard here as we stayed during the first night Grand Prix and more central hotel prices were going through the roof, having stayed more centrally just off Orchard Rd for the first part of our stay venturing to this part of town was quite a contrast - not only the hotel but the lack of clean, pleasant surroundings of the city centre.We checked in and were told as we had booked a standard room we had no windows! it smelt decidedly smokey and the bathroom was a damp wetroom - when you shower everything gets wet. We asked whether there were upgraded rooms available and what the difference was - it just a window so we stayed with what we had but were offered any number of rooms until we were happy with the smell! 2nd room was a bit better, however the lack of windows and virtually non existent extractor fan meant the bathroom was pretty damp - hence the general smell of the hotel.To be fair, the rooms were clean (except for the bathroom damp), however we were not keen on the disposable pillow cases that were provided and some inability to make the beds properly (bottom sheet with about 2 foot spare at the top but plastic of matress uncovered at bottom). TV was provided and one of the rooms we saw had a DVD. No fridge or space, just a bed and one side table, no room to swing a cat! Air con seemed to reset itself to 26degrees everytime you left the room and walls are pretty thin. Lavender MRT was fairly close by.Ultimately, if you don't have to stay here I wouldn't but if you're looking for a real budget option and are not too fussy of your surroundings, it'll do. 
