<Author>vidoodle
<Content>Thank Heavens Singapore is a safe country Before you confirm your booking to this hotel, try to exhaust all other possibilities. Located on 30 Foch Road, this hotel bordering on motel/hostel was not a happy place to return to after a day of sight-seeing and shopping. My friend and I dreaded going back to it - but since we were blessed with a great sense of humor, we soon learned to laugh off its shortcomings. Tip 1 : if you take a cab from the airport, tell the cab driver that hotel 81 elegance is near the Lavender Food Court. Tip 2: Bring your own towels. Tip 3: Request for a room with a window. Negative Side: The location looked a bit dodgy. As my friend and I were both females, we were a bit scared of the area especially since it was our first time in Singapore. From travel guides and travel websites and plain hearsay, we gathered that Singapore was a litter-free and very clean city -- this area disproved that. There were scary-looking folks and massage parlors all over the area. Staff was inconsistent - we'd ask them to call a cab for us from time to time, sometimes the person at the reception would say okay and call one for us while at other times, they'd tell us to hail one from outside the hotel. Strange. The rooms are very very small. Our jaws fell to the uncarpeted floor when we saw the size of the rooms. We could barely move. There was hardly any room for our luggage. The wall was literally one step away from the bed. And to add insult to injury, we were given a room WITHOUT WINDOWS. Talk about claustrophobia. The rooms are obviously not well maintained. There was a crack on the bathroom door and mould on the bathroom tiles. The floor felt dirty and un-swept. The shower area and the toilet have NO PARTITION so schedule your bathroom breaks and shower times wisely! Good thing the place didn't flood. There is a drain on one part of the floor beside the toilet bowl where the shower water goes. Needless to say, the bathroom was always a wet mess after we bathed.The hotel has a very different idea of 'cleaning'. I think their idea of cleaning is making up the bed and maybe wiping up the bathroom floor. My friend and I wanted to see if they really cleaned the room so we'd leave wadded tissue paper under the bed, partially hidden but still obvious. We came back to the hotel and the wadded tissue paper was still there. Other guests were very noisy. In the middle of the afternoon, another guest on our floor decided to blast Crank That Soulja Boy from his/her stereo. This was followed by shouting and door-banging and lots of complaining. Only one electrical socket!No smoking rooms. Nearest MRT station: Farrer Park or Little India.Positive Side:The staff were pretty helpful when it came to booking tours for us. Free candy by the reception. Free water in the room. Hair dryer. The hawkers beside the hotel had pretty good food. Try the Pink Guava and White Fungus drink. Cheers (a convenience store) and 7-11 beside hotel. Bus stop right in front of the hotel - except only or two of the buses that stopped there passed along tourist-friendly routes. 
