<Author>Desparately_seeking
<Content>Cheap but probably best to give it a miss Unfortunately we visited Singapore during an Expo and most of the mid range hotels had bumped up their prices so they were out of our price range.Singapore seems to lack a good stock of budget hotels. We paid around 拢50 direct to stay at the Hotel 81. They are a chain and we chose this one as it was supposed to be their newest property.Location wise it was just 5 minutes walk from two metro stations, which are cheap and easy to use. It's saving grace was its location (opposite) the Lavender Street Food Market where we ate most nights. However, the room was pokey and we had to upgrade to get a window. There was no room to put bags although it was generally clean, the linen and towels were changed everyday and water was restocked.The most iritating thing was the noise - it travelled and it was difficult to sleep with the housekeeping staff (and other guests) banging and crashing outside at all hours. Reception were also not the most helpful. Their abilities only seemed to stretch to ordering a taxi and charging my credit card.It seems you have to be willing to pay much more to stay at a decent hotel in Singapore. 
